  "title": "A Raccoon Nearly Suffocated Inside a Glass Jar",
  "script": "A raccoon nearly suffocated! In Dedham, Massachusetts, a young raccoon stuck its head inside a glass jar and couldn't get it back out. By the time animal control arrived, it was gasping — running out of oxygen, seconds from blacking out. Officers acted fast: a few swift twists, a couple of gentle pulls, the jar came free. They had CPR staged. They had a wildlife rehabilitator on standby. They needed neither. The raccoon blinked, stumbled twice — and then just... climbed a fence, walked across a backyard, and scaled a swing set like nothing happened. The residents who called it in agreed to keep an eye out. It was having a full-on emergency until the moment it wasn't. So: can a raccoon be embarrassed?",
